      "severity": "high",
      "location": "Section 0 — M2.5, esbuild build command",
      "description": "The build command references `src/main.jsx` as the entrypoint in package.json scripts, but the actual file lives at `src/frontend/web/src/main.jsx`. The esbuild CLI command in Section 1 uses the full path, but the npm script in M2.5 uses a relative path. Since package.json lives in `src/frontend/web/`, the correct entrypoint is `src/main.jsx` relative to that directory — BUT the `--outdir=dist` is also relative, which is correct. However, the production command in Section 1 uses absolute repo-relative paths (`src/frontend/web/src/main.jsx`, `src/frontend/web/dist`). These two invocation patterns are inconsistent and will cause CI/CD confusion about working directory expectations.",
