      "severity": "medium",
      "location": "Section 3 — Bottom sheet, focus trap + portal",
      "description": "The spec says bottom sheet uses a portal to document.body, and the focus trap is inside the sheet. But the `inert` management strategy says 'TabBar AND <main> receive inert'. If the portal renders OUTSIDE <main> (which it does — it's on document.body), and you're setting inert on <main>, the portal content is NOT inside an inert subtree, which is correct. But the legacy fallback says 'add aria-hidden to all direct children of <body> except the portal root'. This requires knowing the portal root's DOM identity at the point where you're iterating body children. The spec doesn't define the portal root element's ID or how the inert-management code identifies it.",
